==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antitoxine
<hw>An`ti*tox"ine</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>anti-</ets> +
<ets>toxin</ets>.]</ety> <def>A substance (sometimes the product of a
specific micro-organism and sometimes naturally present in the blood or
tissues of an animal), capable of producing immunity from certain
diseases, or of counteracting the poisonous effects of pathogenic
bacteria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anti-trade</ent>⟦br⟧
